@startuml Execution Engine Flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "SF Mono, Monaco, Consolas, monospace"
skinparam ArrowColor #1a1a1a
skinparam StateBackgroundColor #f0f0f0
skinparam StateBorderColor #1a1a1a

title Execution Engine Flow - Task Planning, Queueing, and Execution

' ============================================================================
' States
' ============================================================================

state "PRD & Spec Approved" as approved #90EE90
state "Task Planner" as planner {
  state "Load Spec Requirements" as load_spec
  state "Generate Task Nodes" as gen_nodes
  state "Build Dependency Graph" as build_dag
  state "Validate DAG\n(Cycle Detection)" as validate
  state "Compute Topological Order" as topo_sort
  state "Persist plan.json" as persist_plan

  load_spec --> gen_nodes : Extract test_plan
  gen_nodes --> build_dag : Create ExecutionTasks
  build_dag --> validate : Link dependencies
  validate --> topo_sort : No cycles
  validate --> [*] : Validation failed\n(exit with error)
  topo_sort --> persist_plan : Deterministic ordering
}

state "Queue Coordinator" as queue {
  state "Load plan.json" as load_plan
  state "Enqueue Entry Tasks" as enqueue_entry
  state "Monitor Dependencies" as monitor_deps
  state "Update Queue State" as update_queue

  load_plan --> enqueue_entry : Read entry tasks
  enqueue_entry --> monitor_deps : Queue JSONL writes
  monitor_deps --> update_queue : Dependency resolution
  update_queue --> monitor_deps : Task status change
}

state "Execution Engine" as execution {
  state "Dequeue Task" as dequeue
  state "Apply Patch/Changes" as apply_patch
  state "Run Validations" as run_validation
  state "Commit to Branch" as commit_branch
  state "Mark Complete" as mark_complete

  dequeue --> apply_patch : Pop from queue
  apply_patch --> run_validation : Git operations
  run_validation --> commit_branch : Lint/test/build
  run_validation --> apply_patch : Auto-fix retry
  commit_branch --> mark_complete : Git commit
  mark_complete --> dequeue : Update queue
}

state "Resume Coordinator" as resume {
  state "Load Last State" as load_state
  state "Read Queue Snapshot" as read_queue
  state "Identify Restart Point" as find_restart
  state "Skip Completed Tasks" as skip_completed

  load_state --> read_queue : feature.json\nlast_step
  read_queue --> find_restart : Queue entries
  find_restart --> skip_completed : Find last success
}

state "Approval Gates" as gates #FFD700
state "Plan Ready" as plan_ready #90EE90
state "Execution Complete" as exec_complete #90EE90
state "Resume Point" as resume_point #FFA500

' ============================================================================
' Transitions
' ============================================================================

[*] --> approved : PRD & Spec\napproval recorded

approved --> planner : CLI: plan generate

planner --> plan_ready : plan.json created\nwith checksum

plan_ready --> queue : CLI: start execution

queue --> execution : Entry tasks queued

execution --> gates : Validation required
gates --> execution : Approval granted
gates --> [*] : Approval denied

execution --> exec_complete : All tasks done

exec_complete --> [*] : Success

' Error/Resume flow
execution --> resume_point : Failure detected
resume_point --> resume : CLI: resume
resume --> queue : Restart from\nlast success
queue --> execution : Continue DAG

' CLI inspection
plan_ready --> [*] : CLI: plan --json\n(inspect without executing)

' ============================================================================
' Notes
' ============================================================================

note right of planner
  **Task Planner (FR-12, FR-13)**
  - Converts spec.json test_plan → ExecutionTask DAG
  - Generates stable task IDs (e.g., I3-T-UNIT-001) derived from requirement IDs
  - Enforces dependency ordering
  - Detects cycles using DFS
  - Computes topological sort (Kahn's algorithm)
  - Persists plan.json with SHA-256 checksum
  - Reuses trace.json ExecutionTask IDs for deterministic traceability

  **Outputs:**
  - plan.json (PlanArtifact schema)
  - plan_metadata.json (hash, entry tasks)
end note

note right of queue
  **Queue Coordinator**
  - Reads plan.json and initializes queue
  - Writes queue entries (JSONL format)
  - Tracks statuses: pending → running → completed
  - Ensures only tasks with satisfied dependencies run
  - Supports idempotent replays

  **Storage:**
  - queue/tasks.jsonl (append-only)
  - In-memory: Map<task_id, ExecutionTask>
end note

note right of execution
  **Execution Engine**
  - Pops tasks from queue (FIFO for same depth)
  - Applies code patches with allowlist enforcement
  - Runs validation commands (lint, test, build)
  - Supports auto-fix retries (max 3 attempts)
  - Commits changes to feature branch
  - Records outputs/diffs in run directory

  **Integrations:**
  - Git adapter (branch, commit, diff)
  - Validation registry (command resolution)
  - Agent adapter (code generation invocation)
end note

note right of resume
  **Resume Coordinator (FR-14)**
  - Loads feature.json (last_step, last_error)
  - Reads queue snapshot (completed vs. pending)
  - Identifies restart point in DAG
  - Skips completed tasks via checksum verification
  - Replays from failure point deterministically

  **Resume Logic:**
  1. Load plan.json
  2. Find last completed task in queue
  3. Mark descendants as pending
  4. Re-enqueue starting from failure
end note

note bottom of gates
  **Approval Gates (ADR-5)**
  - PRD approval → enables spec generation
  - Spec approval → enables plan generation
  - Plan generation → enables execution
  - Validation failures → manual review gate

  **Approval Storage:**
  - approvals.json (append-only log)
  - Approval records reference artifact hashes
end note

@enduml
